# =============================================================================
# ARCHITECTURE OVERVIEW
# =============================================================================
# Backend:  Python 3.11, FastAPI, DuckDB (WAL mode), 43 API route files
#           (364+ endpoints), 72+ services, uvicorn on port 8000
# Frontend: React 18 + Vite + Tailwind CSS (Aurora dark theme) in frontend-v2/
#           14 pages, useApi() hook for all data, Lightweight Charts
# Council:  35-agent DAG in 7 stages with Bayesian-weighted arbiter
#           runner.py (29.4 KB) orchestrates the full pipeline
# Brain:    gRPC + Ollama on PC2 (ProfitTrader, 192.168.1.116, RTX GPU)
# LLM:      3-tier router: Ollama (routine) -> Perplexity (search) -> Claude (deep)
# Events:   MessageBus pub/sub in core/message_bus.py (25 channels)
# Database: DuckDB with connection pooling via data/storage.py get_conn()
# Auth:     Bearer token, fail-closed for live trading endpoints
# Tests:    977+ passing (pytest backend + frontend build), CI GREEN
# Desktop:  Electron app in desktop/ — BUILD-READY
# Infra:    Two PCs — ESPENMAIN (PC1, primary) + ProfitTrader (PC2, GPU)

# =============================================================================
# TRADE PIPELINE (the money path — trace this for any pipeline work)
# =============================================================================
# AlpacaStreamService -> market_data.bar (MessageBus)
#   -> EventDrivenSignalEngine (feature computation + ML scoring)
#   -> signal.generated (score >= regime-adaptive threshold: 55/65/75)
#   -> CouncilGate (invokes 35-agent council)
#     -> Stage 1: Perception + Academic Edge (13 agents, parallel)
#     -> Stage 2: Technical + Data Enrichment (8 agents, parallel)
#     -> Stage 3: Hypothesis + Memory (2 agents, parallel)
#     -> Stage 4: Strategy (1 agent)
#     -> Stage 5: Risk + Execution + Portfolio (3 agents, parallel)
#     -> Stage 5.5: Debate + Red Team (3 agents)
#     -> Stage 6: Critic (1 agent)
#     -> Stage 7: Arbiter (Bayesian-weighted BUY/SELL/HOLD)
#   -> council.verdict
#   -> OrderExecutor (Gate 2b regime -> Gate 2c breakers -> Kelly sizing)
#   -> order.submitted -> WebSocket bridges -> Frontend
#   -> order.filled -> OutcomeTracker -> WeightLearner.update_from_outcome()

# =============================================================================
# COUNCIL AGENTS (35 total across 7 stages)
# =============================================================================
# Core (11): market_perception, flow_perception, regime, social_perception,
#   news_catalyst, youtube_knowledge, hypothesis, strategy, risk, execution, critic
# Academic Edge (12): gex, insider, finbert_sentiment, earnings_tone, dark_pool,
#   macro_regime, supply_chain, institutional_flow, congressional,
#   portfolio_optimizer, layered_memory, alt_data
# Supplemental (6): rsi, bbv, ema_trend, intermarket, relative_strength, cycle_timing
# Debate (3): bull_debater, bear_debater, red_team
# Special: arbiter (Stage 7, deterministic — not counted as voting agent)
#
# VETO_AGENTS = {"risk", "execution"} — ONLY these can veto
# REQUIRED_AGENTS = {"regime", "risk", "strategy"} — must vote non-hold for trade
# New agents should NOT have veto power.

