# =============================================================================
# KNOWN BUGS FROM ARCHITECTURAL REVIEW (verify before assuming fixed)
# =============================================================================
# BUG: Debate history persistence reads wrong attribute
#   runner.py writes to blackboard.debate but reads blackboard.metadata["debate_result"]
#   These are different attributes — debate data may never reach DuckDB.
#
# BUG: _on_outcome_resolved fallback credits ALL agents equally
#   When agent_votes is empty (likely always), it credits 13 hardcoded agent names
#   regardless of what they actually voted. This is anti-learning.
#
# BUG: 20 MessageBus topics are PUBLISH_ONLY (zero subscribers)
#   Events published to these topics are silently dropped.
#   Includes hitl.approval_needed — HITL approvals go nowhere.
#
# BUG: False degradation alerts
#   runner.py has 2 degradation checks — one counts ALL holds (wrong),
#   the other correctly counts only failure-holds (confidence <= 0.0).
#
# BUG: Calibration uses hasattr() monkey-patch — loses data on restart

# =============================================================================
# 17 GITHUB SECURITY ALERTS — must resolve before production
# =============================================================================

# =============================================================================
# CODING RULES (MANDATORY — violating these breaks the system)
# =============================================================================
# 1.  NEVER import or use yfinance — removed from requirements
# 2.  NEVER use mock/fake data in production components
# 3.  ALWAYS use useApi() hook for frontend data — no direct fetch
# 4.  ALWAYS use 4-space indentation in Python — never tabs
# 5.  Council agents MUST return AgentVote schema from council/schemas.py
# 6.  Agent pattern: module-level NAME + WEIGHT + async evaluate() -> AgentVote
# 7.  Features access: f = features.get("features", features); f.get("key", default)
# 8.  CouncilGate is the bridge — signals go through council before OrderExecutor
# 9.  DuckDB: use get_conn() from data/storage.py — never raw connections
# 10. MessageBus for all inter-service events — no direct service calls
# 11. Bearer token auth on all live trading endpoints (API_AUTH_TOKEN)
# 12. ONE repo: Espenator/elite-trading-system — NOT Embodier-Trader
# 13. No secrets in committed files — all keys in backend/.env (gitignored)
# 14. Paths: repo-relative only (backend/, frontend-v2/). See PATH-STANDARD.md
# 15. Run tests before committing: cd backend && python -m pytest --tb=short -q
# 16. Never delete passing tests — fix the underlying code
# 17. Never change council DAG stage order without explicit instruction
# 18. Discovery must be continuous, not polling — scouts publish to swarm.idea
# 19. All frontend pages use Aurora dark theme — cyan/emerald/amber/red palette
# 20. Dashboard route must be inside <DashboardLayout> wrapper in App.jsx

# =============================================================================
# KEY FILES FOR COMMON TASKS
# =============================================================================
# Frontend page:     App.jsx, the page .jsx, hooks/useApi.js, config/api.js
# Backend API:       api/v1/<route>.py, services/<service>.py
# Council/agent:     council/runner.py, council/arbiter.py, council/schemas.py
# Pipeline:          council_gate.py, signal_engine.py, order_executor.py
# Learning:          weight_learner.py, feedback_loop.py
# WebSocket:         websocket_manager.py, frontend-v2/src/services/websocket.js
# Events:            core/message_bus.py
# Auth:              core/security.py, backend/.env
# Startup:           backend/app/main.py (700+ lines, 24 numbered services)
# Config:            config/regime_thresholds.py, council/agent_config.py

